- Python (retriever)
```
retriever/.venv/
**/__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
```

- Native/binary modules (often huge)
```
**/*.node
**/*.wasm
```

- Cache
```
npm-cache/
pnpm-store/
.yarn/
.yarn/cache/
```

Then remove anything already tracked:
```bash
git rm -r --cached node_modules .next .turbo .vercel dist build retriever/.venv
git rm -r --cached "**/*.node" "**/*.wasm"
git add -A
git commit -m "chore: ignore deps/build/binaries to avoid large files"
```

If history already contains big files (e.g., next-swc.darwin-arm64.node), rewrite it before pushing:
```bash
# Install once
brew install git-filter-repo || python3 -m pip install --user git-filter-repo

git filter-repo \
  --path node_modules --path .next --path .turbo --path dist --path build \
  --path retriever/.venv \
  --path-glob '*.node' --path-glob '*.wasm' \
  --invert-paths

git push -f origin main
```

